  "body": "## Description\r\n\r\nI recently set up MEV-Boost for Goerli/Prater. I have several exited validators on Prater (such as https://prater.beaconcha.in/validator/0x8aff2971a436a9a8783fb5574f923bb70b06f74e155961f1b448be0a733230ac5b600e87be1db201ba733cfce57b4660 which was used for slash testing) and during Lighthouse's validator registration process, it sends this validator over to MEV-Boost which causes it to fail.\r\n\r\nAccording to [the official spec](https://ethereum.github.io/builder-specs/#/Builder/registerValidator), only `active` or `pending` validators should be sent to the builder during validator registration.\r\n\r\nHere are MEV-Boost's logs:\r\n```\r\nmev-boost_1      | time=\"2022-08-12T17:56:48Z\" level=info msg=\"http: POST /eth/v1/builder/validators 200\" duration=0.182599993 method=POST module=service path=/eth/v1/builder/validators status=200\r\nmev-boost_1      | time=\"2022-08-12T17:56:51Z\" level=warning msg=\"error calling registerValidator on relay\" error=\"HTTP error response: 400 / {\\\"code\\\":400,\\\"message\\\":\\\"not a known validator: 0x8aff2971a436a9a8783fb5574f923bb70b06f74e155961f1b448be0a733230ac5b600e87be1db201ba733cfce57b4660\\\"}\\n\" method=registerValidator module=service numRegistrations=36 ua= url=\"https://builder-relay-goerli.flashbots.net/eth/v1/builder/validators?id=rocketpool\"\r\nmev-boost_1      | time=\"2022-08-12T17:56:51Z\" level=info msg=\"http: POST /eth/v1/builder/validators 502\" duration=0.101773263 method=POST module=service path=/eth/v1/builder/validators status=502\r\n```\r\n\r\nHere are Lighthouse's BN logs:\r\n```\r\neth2_1           | Aug 12 17:56:51.456 INFO Forwarding register validator request to connected builder, count: 36\r\neth2_1           | Aug 12 17:56:51.560 ERRO Error from connected relay              error: ServerMessage(ErrorMessage { code: 502, message: \"no successful relay response\", stacktraces: [] })\r\neth2_1           | Aug 12 17:56:51.560 WARN Error processing HTTP API request       method: POST, path: /eth/v1/validator/register_validator, status: 500 Internal Server Error, elapsed: 108.337824ms\r\n```\r\n\r\nI [reported this to Flashbots](https://github.com/flashbots/mev-boost/issues/245), who pointed me to the builder API spec above.\r\n\r\nThis issue is also present in [Nimbus](https://github.com/status-im/nimbus-eth2/issues/3961) and [Teku](https://github.com/ConsenSys/teku/issues/6070).\r\n\r\n\r\n## Version\r\nv2.5.1\r\n\r\n## Present Behaviour\r\nLighthouse appears to be sending all of the connected validators to the builder \r\n\r\n## Expected Behaviour\r\nLighthouse should only register validators that are `active` or `pending`\r\n\r\n## Steps to resolve\r\nFilter the validators sent to the builder registration route so only `active` or `pending` ones are sent\r\n",
